      "source": "### Important: Comparing Strings\n\nFor Strings, use `.equals()` instead of `==`:\n- `==` compares if they're the same object in memory\n- `.equals()` compares if they have the same content\n\n```java\nString a = \"hello\";\nString b = \"hello\";\n\na.equals(b)  // true - same content\na == b       // might be true or false depending on how strings were created\n```",
