      "source": "## Summary - What You Learned\n\nIn this part, you learned:\n\n- **`if` statement**: Execute code only when a condition is true\n- **`if-else` statement**: Choose between two options\n- **`if-else-if` ladder**: Check multiple conditions in sequence\n- **Nested `if`**: Put conditions inside other conditions\n- **`switch` statement**: Choose from many specific values\n- **Modern switch expressions**: Cleaner syntax with arrow notation\n\n## Key Points to Remember\n\n1. Conditions must evaluate to `boolean` (true/false)\n2. Use `{}` braces even for single statements (good practice)\n3. For Strings, use `.equals()` not `==`\n4. Don't forget `break` in switch statements!\n5. `default` in switch is like `else` - handles all other cases\n6. Use `&&` (AND) when ALL conditions must be true\n7. Use `||` (OR) when ANY condition can be true\n\n---\n\n### Next Up: Part 5 - Loops\n\nLearn how to repeat code with for, while, and do-while loops!",
